column1: I'm ANTHONY cool and gentle, very simple in nature, easy going with people that are not picky, open mind, very honest. Sometimes more than it should be. I'm passionate about almost any kind of music, for me it's like a kind of expression. I'm passionate about dancing, especially salsa, it just release your soul. Open to changes, you never know what life has for you, and what new lessons are you going to learn, what kind of people are you going to meet and in which way are they going to touch your heart. I am not the Man that breaks heart and looks for the woman to spend the night with but am a man of my Honor and really respect women a lot. I am smarter and more original than that. I am caring, loving and GOD FEARING. If you want a Man that knows how to treat a woman and respect her then read on. I am a hardworking man. I believe we are all living out our own sound tracks. I am a very romantic man, the man that makes everyone laugh, the man you can introduce to your parents. I love the idea of loving someone and giving them all that I have to give. I am the Man that can make you feel like you are the only woman in the room. I want to find a good woman who would be my best friend, my soul mate, my wife, my world, my Angel, my Queen, my lover, my world and everything. One that has a good knowledge about love and cares about family. I want to find that special woman that i cannot wait to get home from work to see her face and have a lovely time with her. I try to be cool always and treat my woman like a Queen. I want my woman that I care for, to know that she is very special to me. I think that the little things add a lot to a relationship. A love note, an unexpected gift or surprise phone call. My personality is my greatest strength, I love to share my life because i am into wide variety of activities and interests. I love kids very much, I adapt well to any situation. column1:
Open minded, liberal in thought (but not in moral values) living, and learning. with each day as it comes... 
I like my life and as it is now I think its time to start sharing (or multiplying) it with someone.  I'm easy to get along unfussy with just about average living habits. 
Just need 4 walls, music, a functioning computer, a floor to sleep on and a square meal. And  my domestic needs are more than satisfied.
Have always been more interested in the functional aspect of things and phenomena rather than their appearances. 
LIkea good read or a movie, watch TV when I get the time. And yes Freinds is funny a lot of the time. THey seem to have really good writers on their staff there.
As for the rest of life, i believe that you either take it on the chin, or take it into your arms. Life will always go on! Make the right choices. 
I'm no poet, and i know it !! Oh I think I just blew it !!!
Sorry about this last bit. Have always professionally been into one form of communication medium or the other. Hence the prolixity of (perhaps) needless words.,"Not a very demanding person, Oh what the the hell, would be disappointed however, if there weren't the occasional demands that I just don't get. And its beautiful !  Then full time attention and affection (just kidding at the last :). I have lived independently for a long time and enjoyed every moment (well almost every moment).

Now would like to share that joy (and sorrrows, for evrynbody gets their fair share in life that need to be dealt with from time to time). But coming back to the joy, yes, I would now like to share (or rather, multiply) it with a practicing dreamer. But more importantly, a woman with a zest for life. An appreciation of all the beautiful things life has to offer and a the chutzpah to go out there and get them (and the act of getting them itself may not be so beautiful sometimes).",,,10 Jun 1969,11:02:00,United Arab Emirates,Mumbai,Average,,,Sindhi,,,,Fair ,,Brother,BE B.Tech (Engineering),"44 yrs, 6ft,

column1: This must be one of the most difficult things I have tried to do. I am attempting to describe in this space a work in progress. ThatAA?A?s how I see myself. I believe that things happen for a reason and the people you meet in life are people you are meant to meet at that point of your life. I have dreams and ambitions but IAA?A?ll leave those for later. I like my work- on good days I feel like a fraud for taking money to do a job that gives me so much pleasure. But this is on good days, on bad days- m not paid enough to put up with the nonsense I have to deal with! I am not a party animal. When I go out I prefer to spend time with people I know well. We could do anything from just staying home, watching a movie, to dancing the night away (been a while since I did that- but I can still remember it!), or experimenting with food. I like eating different cuisines. I have been told that I have an off beat sense of humour. ItAA?A?s kind of weird, sarcastic and sometimes downright dark. It takes getting used to. I cherish my family and friends. I feel blessed and honoured to have them in my life. Stuff I like Music: Santana, Elvis, Kenny Rogers, , Dinsey Movie Tunes, UB40, music with Soul and music I can sing along with.... have to mention I like reading comic strips my favourite-Calvin & Hobbes I love to travel. I have to plan my holidays - lots of places I want to experience; like the Himalayas Hemkund sahab in Himachal, Kashmir, Amazon rain forests, Peru, Venice, Milan, Egypt, Ladak, the small South-East Asian countries where I can backpack, live like a local and just beAA?A.. Work gets in the way!! I relax by hanging out with friends. I can discuss anything on this earth but discussions should not turn into a argument just for the sake of winning. What I am looking for in my soulmate-..... Honesty above all. She must love to cook (need not be edible) so that I can learn from her, know how to have fun, be able to sit still at peace with herself say everything and nothing in silence. A romantic streak would be helpful and appreciated! Must have a wacky sense of humour. Someone who is ready to except her mistakes gracefully AA?A I want my soul to know that bond of sharing a peaceful space with another person.,"What I am looking for in my soul mate: Honesty above all. She must love to cook (need not be edible) so that I can learn from her, know how to have fun, be able to sit still at peace with herself say everything and nothing in silence. For me, family is supreme and always top priority. I am seeking simplicity, humility and sacrifice as the foundations of a lifelong relationship with someone who believes in these traits too. Needless to say, I happily offer all of it myself, and more. I am a person who loves to smile, laugh, live a peaceful life with lots of 'togetherness', have dinner together, chat together. I am intense, I am romantic, but nothing is better to define me than the fact that I am humane. I understand and empathize with pain, maybe because I have seen a lot of it myself. I need someone to hold my hand, who is understanding, who knows what it is like to be cruelly slapped by destiny one sudden day, to be devastated, and how it is to rebuild life, brick by brick against all odds. I am basically a very simple and transparent person and love to see my loved ones smiling. column1:
Thanks for dropping by... I am trying this first time so excuse if it doesn't sound interesting to you.
I am working as a director in a MNC. Earning very decent amount. Have traveled a lot (US, Europe, APAC). We spent about 9 years in US and then decided to settle back in India. We are financially secure and in a very comfortable position. I have 2 lovely kids (12 & 7) Son and daughter. Wife died in a road accident 8 months back. I am single parenting my kids and looking for a suitable match, who is very smart, educated, intelligent and can share and shower her love to all of us.  I guess I am not asking much.
On the lighter side- I am a very fun loving person and want to enjoy life at its fullest. Have good sense of humor and love to dine, party and adventure. I have an athletic body and I love sports and try when ever find time from Home and office :). Last but not the least...I have become a good cook now and can cook many Indian and continental dishes. So people say let me buy dinner for you...I would say I am okay either way - buy or make :). I love comedy/adventure and action movies. I do not like to sit at home on weekends unless we are cooking something special.
If you find this interesting.....do drop a note   and thank you for reading this so far ...appreciate your patience,"I am looking for educated,smart, intelligent girl who can become mother to my two lovely little kids (12& 7) Daughter is 7 years and she really wants a mother who can be her friend and guide.

She should be a good cook as the family is little foodie :)...I am also a good cook BTW. I would prefer as partner,friend and wife who take things as it comes and also wants to lead the live to fullest extent. No one is perfect, so as long as there is understanding, I think we can achieve everything we can. I do not want to write too much on what an idela partner should be.....but its just simple--------

Should be jovial and fun to be with. After all we have 1 life and live it to fullest.",,29 to 35,08 Sep 1969,10:30:00,India,Patna,Average,Slim,1 brother ,Kayastha,Kayastha,,"Birla Institute of Technology (BITS), Mesra",Fair ,Very Fair,Self,MBA/PGDM,"44 yrs, 5ft 8in,

My simplicity and decency describes me and my nature well. Due to my simple nature I have acquired a lot of good things and people around me. 
In my professional life I like being serious and do my work with full commitment. Presently I am working as an accountant in a well known organization. Like everyone I also want to grow in my profession and make my parents feel proud of me. 
One of my major weaknesses is that I am very sensitive.
My mother is a homemaker and father has taken retirement from his profession. My brother is engrossed in the diamond business and doing well. I also have a lovable sister who is married and well settled in her life. 
In my higher education sector I have completed B Com from Gujarat University. 
I dona??t like to share my feelings with many people and like to be reserved when it comes to making friends. Though I have few friends in my life but they are the best part of my life. 
Music is an art of living a peaceful life and avoiding the major complexities and problems of life. Therefore, I like listening to music and also watching movies. Another hobby of mine is travelling to new places.,"The girl to whom I will get married to should be well qualified and settled in her life. I want her to be simple and soft spoken so that both of us can lead a happy and stress free life ahead. My preference will be given to a girl from Gujarat posing a good family background.

She should be flexible enough to fit in my family and once she will enter my family, then she will receive lot of love from them. My family would happily accept her and will not change her as per their thinking.
Only thing I expect from my wife is to respect my parents and other family members. In return her family will also receive complete respect and love from my side.
I will always be there to assist my wife with the tasks at home and outside home. If she is like the one I am looking for then I assure her a happy future ahead.

I was born and educated in London, England, to (BA Hons) level. Yes I am English however I 

I am down-to-earth, grounded, witty, funny, and friendly, hard working and loyal to those that are close to me. I love to laugh - life is too short to worry all the time. I like to stay busy and have a pretty wide range of interests. I love concerts, films, travel, sports. I listen to all types of music, like to read, and take walks to the beach at night (I live very near the beach)

I have 2 brothers and 1 sister they all live in London. We were all born in London, my parents are from Jamaica. I am tall 183 (6ft 2in), slim , athletic build and I am a friendly person.

I have traveled/visited places all over the world Brazil, Colombia, France, America, Thailand, Indonesia, Morocco, Peru, Canada, India and others. I now want someone with me to share these experiences with me.

I do not have any children, I would like to have children soon with the right woman. I do not drink alcohol, smoke cigarettes or take drugs. I am organized and I like to plan for the future, my emotions are stable and I believe in respecting the woman in my life.  I love food from Thailand, Italy, India and Spain

I have my own home in England and my own home in Dubai, I have lived in Dubai for 7 years . I still have much to achieve, I have goals and I am very focused on what I want from life.

I am also a very practical person so what I feel I go with. So that means if it were possible that I really feel you are thatspecial person and you felt the same about me I would not hesitate to come to see you in you in your country.
